\section{Analytic results for the ODEs}
\label{app:Analytic-results-ODEs}


The ODEs \eqref{eq:2eqsFRWdim4}
of Sec.~\ref{Sec:Q-theory-model-of-vacuum-energy-decay}
can be solved analytically if the following variable is used:

where `$\ln$' is the natural logarithm and
$a(\tau)$ the FRW cosmic scale factor.
Since the Hubble parameter $h$ (assumed positive)
corresponds to the rate of change
of the scale factor, $h(\tau)=\dot{a}/a$,
we have that $h^{-1}\,d/d\tau$ equals $d/d\xi$.
Furthermore, we take the time derivative of ODE \eqref{eq:EinsteinFRWdim4}
and write the resulting second-order ODE as a
pair of first-order ODEs.
The three first-order ODEs are then
\begin{subequations}\label{eq:3eqsFRW}
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{d}{d\xi}\, r_{V}   &=&  -4\, \gamma\, r_{V}^2\,,
\label{eq:3eqsFRW-rV-prime}
\[2mm]
\frac{d}{d\xi}\, k   &=& -2\, \gamma\, k^2 \,,
\label{eq:3eqsFRW-k-prime}
\[2mm]
h \frac{d}{d\xi}\, h +2\,h^2    &=&  k \,,
\label{eq:3eqsFRW-h-prime}
\end{eqnarray}
\end{subequations}
where $k=\dot{h} +2\,h^2$ is proportional to the Ricci scalar $R$
of the spatially-flat FRW universe considered.

The solution of the ODEs \eqref{eq:3eqsFRW} is given by
\begin{subequations}\label{eq:3eqsFRW-sol}
\begin{eqnarray}
r_{V}(\xi)   &=& \frac{1}{4\gamma\,(\xi-\xi_{0})} \,,
\label{eq:3eqsFRW-rV-sol}
\[2mm]
k(\xi)    &=& \frac{1}{2\gamma\,(\xi-\xi_{0})}\,,
\label{eq:3eqsFRW-k-sol}
\[2mm]
h(\xi)   &=&
\sqrt{\exp[-4\,\xi]\,\Big(C_{1}+\exp[4\,\xi_{0}]\; \text{Ei}\,[4\,\xi-4\,\xi_{0}] \Big)\Big/\gamma} \,,
\label{eq:3eqsFRW-h-sol}
\end{eqnarray}
\end{subequations}
with two integration constants, $\xi_{0}$ and $C_{1}$, and
the exponential integral function \text{Ei}\,[y], for $y>0$
defined by~\cite{AbramowitzStegun}

